sql:
SELECT COUNT(license_id) 
FROM licenses 
WHERE license_type = 'open-source';

SELECT licenses.license_id, licenses.license_name
FROM licenses
JOIN project_licenses ON licenses.license_id = project_licenses.license_id;

SELECT license_type, COUNT(license_id) AS license_count
FROM licenses
GROUP BY license_type;

external_knowledge:
- "garden of innovation" refers to the collection of projects;
- "wise gardeners" symbolizes the project managers;
- "bloom of progress" symbolizes modifications;
- "type of bloom's nectar" refers to different types of project licenses;
- "density of the garden's ecosystem" metaphorically describes the complexity of the projects as represented by the natural logarithm of the modifications.

sql:
SELECT project_id, COUNT(license_id) AS total_licenses
FROM project_licenses 
GROUP BY project_id;

external_knowledge:
- "Beacon names": refers to the project names;
- "Light status": indicates the compliance status of the project;
- "Lighthouse keepers": refers to the project managers;
- "Navigators guiding their compliance": refers to the compliance officers.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS Total_Compliance_Audits
FROM compliance_audits
WHERE audit_type = 'scheduled' AND result = 'Compliant';

SELECT modified_by_id, AVG(modification_id) AS 'Average Modifications per User'
FROM modifications
GROUP BY modified_by_id;

SELECT DISTINCT u.username
FROM users u
INNER JOIN modifications m ON u.user_id = m.modified_by_id;
